OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FMainly dry with early morning
OL,6,Fcloud soon burning off to leave a warm
OL,7,Fand sunny day. However staying rather
OL,8,Fcloudy for western coasts where the
OL,9,Fodd light shower is possible.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FMainly dry and a fine end to
OL,12,Fthe day for many, although cloudier
OL,13,Faround the west coast. Patchy rain
OL,14,Fpossible developing in the west
OL,15,Fovernight.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FSome drier and brighter
OL,18,Fspell around Inverness, Speyside and
OL,19,Fthe Black Isle, but mostly cloudy with
OL,20,Foutbreaks rain, the rain turning heavy
OL,21,Fand perhaps thundery at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
